When the proof can be `rfl`, the proof should be `rfl`.
```suggestion
    (F ◁ η).app X = η.app (F.obj X) := rfl
```
Could you do the same modification for the other lemmas (above and below this one)? Could you also add similar lemmas for the associator and unitors?
Will we really need similar lemmas for associators and unitors? Because since `Cat` is a strict bicategory there are already simp-lemmas that replace these by eqToIsos.
(although their proofs are by aesop_cat and not rfl, so maybe thats a reason to add them here)
